<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="275" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/590</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Spring
                                        Rice</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-06">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 6, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 8.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I did not fail to
                                telegraph to <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir E. Grey</persName> in
                                the sense of your letter of the 5th relative to rosin. As you are
                                aware, cargoes of rosin shipped prior to the declaration that rosin
                                was contraband (with a reasonable delay), although they may be
                                seized, can not be confiscated but must be paid for, if seized, in
                                full.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cecil Spring Rice</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>